  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to Prove that injection of 15 to 20 mL of lidocaine 1% into the
      fracture site (Hematoma block) is more effective in terms of pain relieving then injection of
      10 mL of lidocaine 2%, and equally safe in terms of complications, for closed reduction of
      distal radius fractures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
